I am willing to pay $29 as that fits my budget just now.

I can do $32 last. Would that work?
Okay, now let's set up a time for me to come over to your house to do the work.

events.data: Hi - I saw your bike posted and would like more information on it please. how are the tires?
Thank you for your interest. They were recently replaced and are in excellent shape.
Ok - is this a 10, 12, 18 or 21 speed?
This is a 21 speed.
It is difficult to see from the one picture - does this have disc brakes?
It has Avid Juicy 7 Hydraulic Disc Brakes
would you consider anything for trade?
Not at this time, but if it helps I'd be willing to deliver the bike to you and allow you to try it out.
Ok, I live in Bogota, Columbia, South America, so the trip may be costly.
You're in luck.  We're planning a trip to Bogota, Columbia.
Wow - what luck! Ok, since the bike is 8 years old, I can offer $650 for it. Is that something you would consider?
That's a serious offer, but the bike cost far more than that new and it has been maintained properly.  I'm also bringing it to you which shaves a lot off of delivery costs.  $700 sounds better to me.
Can we make offer contingent upon seeing it in person, and trying it out? If it looks good, then I will pay 700
That works for me.  Worst case scenario I'll use the bike on the trip.
thanks alot - see you in Bogota!
Thank you! See you soon.

$1000 is way too low. How about $1500?

Description: I'm selling my beloved Soma Smoothie in 54cm, due to finally realizing that the fit just doesn't work for me.

events.data: Good evening.  Hope you are well.  I am interested in an apartment.  I saw the listing, and am wondering if this is a 1, 2 or 3 bedroom apartment?
We have all thee options available right now, although at this time we only have a couple of 3 bedroom apartments. How many bedrooms are you looking for?
I would most likely be interested in a two bedroom apartment.  If we could get a unit with a walk-in pantry, I would be willing to offer $2,000 for it.

Our two bedroom units are priced at $2,300. It includes the heat, water and garbage. These apartments have great floor plans with walk-in pantry and all new appliances. Would you like to come take a tour?

I would love to come take a tour.  I am just concerned that $2,300 might be a little too steep for me to afford right now.  I am a landscaper by trade.  Is there anyway I would be able to provide my landscaping services for Garden Village Apartments in return for getting the apartment at $2,000?  I do really nice work!

We have a contract with our own landscaping company. We can offer you $100 discount per month if you sign a 12 months lease, providing that your application is approved. I think you will be impressed with our property and all the amenities that we offer.
That sounds reasonable.  I will be willing to go for the $2,200 per month, with a 12 month lease.

Great! Please let me know when you would like to come take a tour. Also please bring your picture ID and your income verification (2 latest pay stubs or bank statement). Looking forward to seeing you.
I can be there this weekend, and will bring the id and income verification.

events.data: Hello
Hi. I would love to get rid of this bike soon. It is 800 and a great price, seeing that it cost much more when it was originally purchased.
I'm looking at getting this for my son for his birthday. Can you tell me if there is anything wrong with the bike?
There is nothing wrong with the bike. I'm only selling it because I had surgery, gained weight, and am too big for the bike. I think your son will love it! I only rode it twice, making it like new.
Did anyone own it before you?
I am the only owner. I would like to sell it for $800. How does that price sound to you?
I was hoping closer to $600. Is there any room to work?

Of course! I want your son to have it and for you to get a great price on it. Since I want 800 and you want 600, let's meet in the middle at 700. I'll even include a bid red bow and brand new helmet for your son!
He'll appreciate the bow. You throw in a new pair of tires with the helmet and ill do $700.
For new tires, I'd have to do 725. $725 includes new tires, a helmet, and a red bow. Is that a deal? If so, please make an offer.
I think $700 is the most I can do for an 8-year old bike.

Description: Gently Aligns the Spine
Safely Releases Pressure and Tension
Relieves Back Pain

Back2Life's Continuous Passive Motion releases the pressure to relieve the pain, increasing flexibility in your muscles and repositioning the vertebrae into correct anatomical alignment for long-term relief. Doctors and physical therapists often use Continuous Passive Motion to help patients suffering from conditions like sciatica, herniated discs, and back spasms. This method is designed to give you results gradually, safely, and easily.

Just two 12-minute sessions per day repeated over the course of a few days, weeks, or months - depending on your individual makeup and the severity of your condition - will have a cumulative impact on the health of your back and your overall quality of life.

events.data: Hey, I'm interested in this item but I'm on a budget. Is your list price your final offer?
This bike is a great deal as you can see from the description.  I feel as though $800 is a reasonable asking price considering the high end components.
The frame looks great, but I'm concerned about maintenance costs and more fragile components.
Would you be interested if I delivered it to you for free and dropped the price to $775?
Free delivery is a perk to me, but I think the parts you've listed are only worth about $500.
That is a very big discount.  I will add free delivery, maintenance for three months and a final price of $750.
That's not a very big price drop. What about $600?
The lowest I will go is $700 and no other perks.
That's just too high for me. Are you sure?
$700 is more than fair.
Can you tell me anything more about the bike that will convince me of that? All I see is a 2009 aluminum frame, the crankset, and the handlebars and stem.
It has Shimano Devore XT crankset, Ritchie's Comp handlebars and stem, Avid Juicy 7 Hydrolic Disc Brakes.  These are all high end components.
Ah, I didn't know about the brakes! That makes a big difference for me. I'm willing to pay $650, in cash if you'd prefer, and pick it up myself.
$690 and it is yours.
Are you willing to go just a bit lower, perhaps $675?
Ok, it's a deal at $675!
I agree! But for some reason, I can't submit the offer from my end. Are you able to do so?
Yup, I'm submitting right now.
I figured it out.

Would that be the new blue book value or used blue book value?
Used, it's mostly because it's a Lexus with all the amenities and add-ons. I figure it's decent to give it for 7500 because of the history of a fender bender
Do you have all of the service records for it?
Yup, and the title
I can offer you 5200 cash
I need 6000, is that in your price range?
6000 is abit above my prince range.  I'm sure the accident is not noticeable but I really can go no more than 5250
I'm sorry I already made the final offer. I need 6000 minimum because of all the add-ons purchased and the work from the accident.
I thought you said it was a minor fender bender? How much work was done on it from the accident.  And what type of add-ons?

Like from the original purchase price, if I were to give it to you for 5k, that's the cost of a Yaris with no camera, gps navigation, and the couple hundred dollars I sunk into getting the fender bender professionally fixed.
Oh, it has a camera?  Is that a back-up camera?

Yup, it has a nice back-up camera so you never hit anything, decent included sound system as is with Yaris, the moonroof/sunroof all work and were barely used, as well as the power liftgate/power windows
ok since it has a backup camera I don't mind paying 6,000 for the car.

Description: This is an awesome bike trailer for your kid.   It features 7 shiftable gears so that your kid can learn to shift but more importantly shift down or up to continue to help you pedal the bike.    I know that without the shiftable gears my kid would either think the pedaling was too hard at times or going so fast they couldn't feel their pedaling helping. Good doing business with you.

Hi.. I am really interested in your North Fremont home. It is a convenient location for me. The price, however, is higher than the surrounding homes in the area. I would like to negotiate the prive with you.
I'm willing to negotiate.

Great. Unlike most tenants who may party which can lead to damages. I am a solitary homebody. I do not smoke, party or have parties. If you're willing to keep the grounds immaculate, I'd be willing to go down to 2800 dollars per month.
That is still more than I can afford. I am trying to save in order to hopefully buy my own house. I will tend to the grounds weekly and I can install the carpet myself. I can pay $2000 a month.
I'm sorry, that is too low for a rental in this area. 2500 is my final offer.
Would you consider $2100.
No, sorry. $2500 is as low as I can go.
I'm sorry .. That is just more than I can afford.
I'm sorry too, but $2100 is too low for me. If you can't afford $2500 then unfortunately I don't think we can negotiate.
Can we meet in the middle at $2300. I may be able to cut back on some expenses.
No, I'm sorry.

Description: Gently Aligns the Spine
Safely Releases Pressure and Tension
Relieves Back Pain

Back2Life's Continuous Passive Motion releases the pressure to relieve the pain, increasing flexibility in your muscles and repositioning the vertebrae into correct anatomical alignment for long-term relief. Doctors and physical therapists often use Continuous Passive Motion to help patients suffering from conditions like sciatica, herniated discs, and back spasms. This method is designed to give you results gradually, safely, and easily.

Just two 12-minute sessions per day repeated over the course of a few days, weeks, or months - depending on your individual makeup and the severity of your condition - will have a cumulative impact on the health of your back and your overall quality of life.

events.data: Hello!   Do you have any questions about the Prius?
How many miles does it have on it? You say "had backup camera" does it work?

There are 180,000 miles on the car, mainly highway.  It is a good runner.    It does have a backup camera, but only works when it wants to.   I don't use it often so I never got it looked at for repair.
How many miles does it have on it? You say "had backup camera" does it work?
I need something reliable. It does have a lot of miles on it. Mostly highway though. Would you accept 2100?
It is a very reliable car.    It does have higher miles, however Toyota's are very well known for lasting.    I'm not able to accept $2,100, that is too low, less than half of what I'm asking.
I need something reliable. It does have a lot of miles on it. Mostly highway though. Would you accept 2100?
I will need to have some work done on it, it sounds like. Maybe an electrical problem somewhere. Its for my daughter, she's going to college next month. How old are the tires?
This would be a great car for her!    Tires I replaced about 3 months ago, and only have about 2,000 miles on them.   They are a very good all weather tire.
Sweet. Okay. I can go as high as $2250. But that's really all I can afford at this time.
I will need to have some work done on it, it sounds like. Maybe an electrical problem somewhere. Its for my daughter, she's going to college next month. How old are the tires?
I can't go that low, unfortunately.     The tires alone are practically new, and were $700 new.     I can drop it to $3,900.
Sweet. Okay. I can go as high as $2250. But that's really all I can afford at this time.
Or, if it helps, I can take the $2,250 as a deposit and hold for you for a month so you can come up with the rest of the money.
That's too steep for me at this time. I still would have to make sure it is roadworthy. That's really nice of you but I will need that month to get it ready for her to take to college.
Ok, let me know if you change your mind.   I would love to help you out, but I can't go for half of what I'm asking.

item.Title: 2001 Honda Civic LX Sedan 4-Door Auto -Only 60k Miles -Clean Carfax

events.data: Hello, I'm interested in your Civic, can you tell me more about it?
Good little car, great gas mileage. Only 60k original miles. I used it to commute to back and forth to work. No issues that I can think of, just a nice little car that is cheap to drive.
What kind of gas mileage does it get?
I am averaging around 30 city/ 37 highway.
That's good, but I'm not so sure I want to pay so much for such an old car. How about $4600?

I couldn't come down nearly that low. Car is in great shape, and only 60k miles. This car is good for at least another 140k miles, perhaps more with really good care. I could come down to $6000 if that helps you.
I suppose I could stretch that much in a month or two, but right now the most I can do is $5500.
Cash in hand, you pick up today, I will go to $5500.
Sounds good. Thanks for negotiating.

events.data: hello, are you interested in this apartment complex?
I am, how much is a 2 bedroom, the ad doesn't specify bedrooms available

Oh I see, and how much is a 1 bedroom?

That's too bad, I'm on a tight budget.  Would you be willing to accept me for $600 per month?

There is unfortunately no way for me to lower the price that low but, what I can do for you is waive the pet deposit and give you 3 visits free to our pet spa. You can also save money by cancelling your gym membership since we have one on-site included in your monthly rent!

My budget will allow me to go up to $650 only but I have a proposition.  I own my own construction company.  I would be able to have my crew fix any repairs as long as I'm living there, FREE OF CHARGE!  That would save you hundreds, maybe thousands over the year! What do you say, $650?

events.data: Hi are you interested in the apartment?
I am.  what size is it?
We have multiple sizes avaible to lease, our most popular option is the 2 bedroom, 2 bath option and that includes full utilities.
oh ok so is it the 2/2 that is 979?
Yes it is. Are you attending Berkeley as a student?
Actually A teaching internship.  Do you have say a studio available?  I really have no use for something so big and was hoping to stay more in the $400 range.
We do have studios avaiable for lease. Our studios are top of line and perfect for residents who only need a single room.
That is really what I need what is the price on those?
We are currently leasing studios at $979 a month but I'm willing to bargain with you if you can move in soon.
Wait your studios are the same price as your 2 bed 2 bath how does that work?
Yes they are but the studios are around the same size as the 2 bed 2 bath apartments and the studios have balcony access and special parking permits.
Wow that is a big studio.  Well as I said I was trying to stay around 400 I could do 550 since it does include utilites.  If you can work with that price I will even sign a 2 year lease.
Okay I can $550 if you sign the 2 year lease and agree to move in by the end of this month.

I know that without the shiftable gears my kid would either think the pedaling was too hard at times or going so fast they couldn't feel their pedaling helping.  It took some time to teach them but definitely the way to go.   I highly suggest a shiftable trailer over the non-shifting one.

events.data: Hi how are you today
Hi, I am good and you?
Im great.  Are you interested in the bike trailer?
I am. Can you tell me how old this is? What condition is it in?
Funny story actually.  My neighbor backed over my old one so his insurance bought be a new one.  My son is too old for it now so the one that i am selling is brand new, has never even been used.
Oh my! Well, I am a single mother and my child could really use this. Would you be willing to come down on the price considering you got a brand new replacement for your used one?
actually I had pulled out the old one to sell and was going to ask $100 for that one so that is why I am asking that for this one.  But how much were you thinking?
How would you sell the old one if it was run over by the neighbor?
They ran it over while I was having a garage sale.  I was asking 100 for it at that sale.  After the accident I did not try to sell it
I can do $60 for this one. I could get it today with cash in hand.
If we can meet in the middle at $80 we have a deal.
$75 is the highest I can go at this time.
deal

Description: This is an awesome bike trailer for your kid.   It features 7 shiftable gears so that your kid can learn to shift but more importantly shift down or up to continue to help you pedal the bike.    I know that without the shiftable gears my kid would either think the pedaling was too hard at times or going so fast they couldn't feel their pedaling helping.  It took some time to teach them but definitely the way to go.   I highly suggest a shiftable trailer over the non-shifting one.

events.data: Hello! I'm interested in your Toyota. It looks great. Is there anything wrong with it?
The car runs as would be expected of a car of such mileage. No problems sir!
Oh great! I see from the ad that it is very clean. Is there any damage?
No damage. And it has passed the smog check.
Great. What's the reason why you are trying to get rid of it?
I am a dealer and I want another driver to have a great experience with this car.
I see. How many miles are on the car?
170,000 and such 5700 is a more than fair price.
That's quite a bit. Are you willing to negotiate for a lower price?
of course. what is your budget like?
I've been looking for a car ranging from 2.5K to 4K. I am looking at a few other cars too. Would 3K work for you?
I will need 5000 to part ways with this one. But what we can do is that i can get 1000 down from you and the rest can be paid monthly.
How about $3500 in cash today. If there are no issues after 3 months, I'll give you an extra $500?
I just don't see it my friend. I cant make money off of that. It is in great condition. Ready to go. 4500 would be where we need to be at.
Sorry, that's out of my budget. I'll check out the other cars I had in mind. Thank you for your time.
Good luck.

events.data: Hello I see you have an apartment for rent
Yes, it's 2200 a month.
Could you tell me about the amenities?
Well, it's close to the UC Berkeley campus, so if you are a student, It's close to where you need to be. There's plenty to do in the area.
Yes, that's my school, so that's convenient. Could you tell me what kind of food is available at the Durant Food Court?
I'll put it this way: it has everything. It's very diverse in it's cultural representation.
Oh great! So there's 1 bedroom, is laundry included?
Not on the site but there is a couple of them within a few blocks.
Oh darn, that's sort of inconvenient. Could you come down on the price a little since I'll have to travel to the laundromat and pay for the coin machines? I was thinking $1550
Yeah, that'd be a little too low for us. We could do 2100 and throw in free internet.

That's just too high. I get internet on my phone so I don't need that. It's really difficult for me to get around due to a disability so the laundry being so far means I'll have to take a cab + pay the laundry machines. I could do $1,700 but no more
I understand, I am myself disabled and I know how tough it is to find affordable housing. How about this. We will cover your utilities if you can do 2000
